==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: obscurity
<hw>ob*scu"ri*ty</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧b*sk⟦umac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>obscuritas</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>obscurit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
obscure.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> darkness; privacy; inconspicuousness;
unintelligibleness; uncertainty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are not for <qex>obscurity</qex> designed.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were now brought forth from <qex>obscurity</qex>, to be
contemplated by artists with admiration and despair.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Darkness; dimness; gloom. See
<er>Darkness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>obsecrate</ent>⟦br⟧
